This paper deals with the complexity of reasoning in abstract argumentation frameworks, which is a topic closely related to artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves graph theory and computational complexity, which suggests that cs.LG and cs.DS are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the polynomial hierarchy and hardness of reasoning problems, which are topics that fall under cs.CC. Finally, the paper deals with argumentation frameworks, which is a topic that falls under cs.CR.
